The article discusses how Obamacare, also known as the Affordable Care Act, imposes a tax on low-income families. It states that more than one in three households that are taxed under Obamacare earn less than $25,000, which is around the federal poverty line for a family of four. Additionally, over 75% of penalized households earn less than $50,000 and nine out of ten earn less than $75,000. The article argues that these households are being forced to pay a fine to avoid purchasing a product they either do not want or cannot afford. It also mentions that Obamacare has negatively impacted the private market, which previously provided options that were more suitable for these individuals.